data.name: lblRules.Text
data.value: The grid above lists all Windows firewall rules. The ones prefixed by "Custom rules" have been created by Windows Firewall Notifier. You can not manually create rules, but you can remove useless ones if required.

data.name: lblConnections.Text
data.value: This screen displays all active connections on this computer, updated every second (by default). Closed connections (in orange) will remain displayed a few seconds before disappearing.

data.name: lblLog.Text
data.value: This page displays a list of the latest blocked outgoing connections (for performance reasons, the list has been limited to 500 items). If you need a complete list, please use the Windows events log viewer.

data.name: lblExceptions.Text
data.value: The Exceptions tab lists all programs you decided to always block when not using the "Create a blocking rule instead of an exceptions list" setting (see Notifications Settings). Those "exceptions" are used by Windows Firewall Notifier to filter which notifications have still to be shown; this list can be modified if needed. No firewall rule is created nor removed when you update this list.
